      "id": "PopularPost285859",
      "post_content": "Card of the Day, December 13th, 2012  \nWrecking Ball is instant speed land destruction, of which you don't see much. I think this is probably because some players would try to destroy a land in response it being tapped for mana, which you can't do, and so to avoid the whole confusion, Wizards usually prints sorcery speed LD. The same type of deal goes for instant speed discard, which is also pretty rare (as in, not that common, er, not that frequently appearing on cards...)  \nNowadays you hardly see any good LD getting printed. There is usually about one spell per set that takes care of lands, and it is usually pretty unplayable. This is sad because there are some pretty outrageous lands out there in standard (I'm looking at you, [Cavern of Souls](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Cavern of Souls) and shocklands). But I guess land destruction just isn't fun. Or even necessary. Just let everyone play 5 colors with no circumstances whatsoever, huh?  \nOh, and this card destroys creatures, too? ",
      "posted_by": "pedrodyl",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost285859\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\">Card of the Day, December 13th, 2012<br/>Wrecking Ball is instant speed land destruction, of which you don't see much. I think this is probably because some players would try to destroy a land in response it being tapped for mana, which you can't do, and so to avoid the whole confusion, Wizards usually prints sorcery speed LD. The same type of deal goes for instant speed discard, which is also pretty rare (as in, not that common, er, not that frequently appearing on cards...)<br/>Nowadays you hardly see any good LD getting printed. There is usually about one spell per set that takes care of lands, and it is usually pretty unplayable. This is sad because there are some pretty outrageous lands out there in standard (I'm looking at you, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Cavern of Souls\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Cavern of Souls\">Cavern of Souls</a> and shocklands). But I guess land destruction just isn't fun. Or even necessary. Just let everyone play 5 colors with no circumstances whatsoever, huh?<br/>Oh, and this card destroys creatures, too? </span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '285859'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy